<paragraph id="8B96369BFFA7E27A35E5AFF9FCD2FAD4" blockId="7.[151,1437,941,1435]" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">
Diagnosis. Medium-sized (
<quantity id="4CD19B7EFFA7E27A34D8AFF9FD31FB7F" box="[506,648,1157,1184]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.949999999999999" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" unit="mm" value="6.949999999999999" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="6.1">6.1–7.8 mm</quantity>
), dark bronze, frons with short, erect, yellow-brown pubescence, lateral sides of pronotum and elytra with long, rusty pubescence; elytra rather strongly wedge-shaped, often weakly caudiform; ventral surface bronze with short, white, recumbent pubescence; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFA7E27A314AAFB1FB03FB38" box="[1128,1210,1229,1255]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) long, almost parallel-sided at basal two thirds, parameres without preapical spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFA7E27A35E5AE69FE78FAA7" blockId="7.[151,1437,941,1435]" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">
Differential diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A34E8AE69FD2CFAF0" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[458,661,1301,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilifrons">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A34E8AE69FD2CFAF0" box="[458,661,1301,1327]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">Anthaxia pilifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A3644AE6AFC54FAF0" authorityName=": Bily" authorityYear="1985" box="[870,1005,1301,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komareki">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3644AE6AFC54FAF0" box="[870,1005,1301,1328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">A. komareki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs by the narrower vertex, shallow lateroposterior depressions, longer anntennomeres of male and by the shape of male genitalia (see also key and 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A3408AE22FE09FAA8" authorityName=": Bily" authorityYear="1985" box="[298,432,1373,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komareki">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3408AE22FE09FAA8" box="[298,432,1373,1400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">A. komareki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
